This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on automatic speech recognition (ASR) and sequence modeling problems. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of recurrent neural networks and convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing tasks. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with speech recognition and acoustic modeling. 

Furthermore, it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the use of deep learning approaches and deep residual learning. 

It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as ASR is a subfield of AI and the paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it focuses on the use of neural networks for ASR.
